# Terraform Module Standards

## File Layout

Every module directory must contain:
- `main.tf` — primary resources
- `variables.tf` — all inputs with `type`, `description`, and `default` where appropriate
- `outputs.tf` — all outputs with `description`

Never declare variables inline in resource files.

## Variable Declarations

```hcl
# BAD
variable "vpc_id" {}

# GOOD
variable "vpc_id" {
  description = "ID of the VPC to deploy into"
  type        = string
}
```

## Tagging

Accept `project` and `environment` variables. Tag every taggable resource:

```hcl
locals {
  common_tags = {
    Project     = var.project
    Environment = var.environment
    ManagedBy   = "terraform"
  }
}

resource "aws_vpc" "this" {
  cidr_block = var.vpc_cidr
  tags       = merge(local.common_tags, { Name = "${var.project}-${var.environment}-vpc" })
}
```

## Naming

- Use `this` or `main` as the logical resource name when a module manages a single instance.
- AWS resource names: `${var.project}-${var.environment}-<component>`.
- Never hardcode region, AZs, or account IDs — accept them as variables.

## Outputs

Always output IDs, ARNs, and DNS names that downstream modules or root modules need:

```hcl
output "vpc_id" {
  description = "The VPC ID"
  value       = aws_vpc.this.id
}
```
